      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKI MARK (8) continued his good form when runner-up here last week, beaten 2 metres. That was his fourth placing from his last five starts so his hoof is on the till. Drawn to enjoy an economical run and the sprint lane is in play so could break though. ARRAPS (9) placed two starts ago then started favourite last time but things went amiss when he broke and finished 4.6 metres away. Proven here and is a player with manners and even luck. ATOMIC GLORY (7) has been about the mark of late and must be respected having added to a series of top-four results when beaten only 2.8m last week at Melton. MAJOR MAURIE (5) draws lower than last start and owns a good record at this distance.",
